service.name: Cleft Lip and Cleft Palate Scheme
service.description: The Cleft Lip and Cleft Palate Scheme helps with treatment costs for specialised services for cleft lip and cleft palate conditions. The Scheme provides Medicare benefits for a range of dental treatment provided by certain eligible practitioners, including: some orthodontic work; simple and surgical extraction of teeth; some general and prosthodontic services by your family dentist; oral and maxillofacial surgery.
